data.meta_description: MK40 4JW is a primarily residential postcode in Queens Park, Bedford. Check typical house prices, council tax bands, business rates, broadband availability and local schools. Find nearby hotels and holiday rentals.
data.text:
Summary

MK40 4JW is a primarily residential postcode in Queens Park, Bedford. It was first introduced in January 1980.

The most common council tax bands are B and A.

Residential buildings are typically terraced (including end-terrace) and detached. Domestic properties are mostly houses and flats.

Estimated residential property values, based on historical transactions and adjusted for inflation, range from £94,897 to £656,738 with an average of £176,521.

Residential buildings were typically constructed between 1900 and 1929 and before 1900.

None of the residential properties sold since 1995 have been new builds or newly converted.

Domestic properties are mostly a mix of owner occupied and privately rented.

The most common Energy Performance Certificate (EPC) ratings are D and E.

Commercial rateable values range from £1,200 to £7,100 with an average of £3,456. The most common recorded business types are Shop and Advertising Right.

Bedford is a town, which had a population of 87,590 in the 2011 census.

In the 2011 census, there were 101 people resident in MK40 4JW, of which 59 were male and 42 were female. This also includes overnight visitors at domestic properties, and residents of non-domestic properties such as hotels, prisons and halls of residence.

MK40 4JW is in the Bedford travel to work area. NHS services are provided by the Bedfordshire Primary Care Trust.

MK40 4JW is approximately 30m (98ft) above sea level.
